# ==============================================================================

# REPOMIX EXCLUSIONS (D:\source\SPG)

# ==============================================================================

# 1. Redundant Backup & Legacy Files

# Your file tree shows old project configurations.

# If the AI reads multiple csproj layouts, it gets confused about the active setup.

_.csproj.old
_.csproj.old.\*
\*.sln.old

# 2. Build & Deploy Folders

# If your "artifacts" folder contains builds, logs, or pipeline outputs, block it.

artifacts/
bin/
obj/

# 3. Godot Text-Data Bloat (Crucial for Token Saving)

# Godot .tscn (scenes) and .tres (resources) are technically text files,

# so Repomix will pack them. However, large scenes contain thousands of lines of

# raw node transforms, collision arrays, and vector bakes that choke LLM context.

_.tscn
_.tres

# 4. Auto-Generated or Transient Scripts

# From your screenshot, these look like transient/baked shader or engine scripts.

_fog_\*.gd

# 5. Non-Code Metadata (Optional Token Savers)

LICENSE
\*.txt
!repomix-snapshot.txt # Handled externally now anyway
